# 🔧 Exact changes (keep your tone, fix the risk)

## 1. PAYMENT + RETAINER LANGUAGE (high priority)

### Current:

> “A 50% deposit holds your date…”

### Change to:

> “A 50% retainer holds your date, with the balance due two weeks before the wedding.”

✅ Aligns with contract  
✅ Avoids refund misunderstanding  
✅ Better legally

***

## 2. CANCELLATION (⚠️ biggest legal mismatch)

### Current FAQ:

> “Cancel more than two months out and you get the full deposit back…”

❌ This directly conflicts with:

* your contract (non-refundable retainer)
* accepted industry / ACL-safe structure

***

### Replace ENTIRE answer with:

> “Weddings move, and I get that. If you need to cancel or postpone, just let me know as early as you can. I try to be fair and reasonable, and the details depend on timing and whether I am able to rebook the date. Full terms sit in your booking agreement.”

✅ Keeps tone  
✅ Doesn’t overpromise  
✅ Stops legal contradiction  
✅ Pushes detail into contract (correct place)

***

## 3. GUARANTEED NUMBERS (soften slightly)

### Current:

> “I commit to at least 9 pieces an hour.”  
> “The number you book is the number you get.”

This is **almost fine**, but legally it reads as a **hard guarantee**.

***

### Safer version:

> “I aim for around 9 pieces an hour. The number you book is the number I plan for, and anyone I do not reach on the night, I finish in the studio afterwards and post to you.”

✅ Keeps certainty  
✅ Removes hard guarantee risk  
✅ Still commercially strong

***

